SEMDL Help Topic: reference set

Usage:
- `ssd set path:<id>.<field> <value> --dry-run <file>`
- `ssd set meta:<id>.<field> <value> --dry-run <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id> <field> <value> <file>`

Purpose:
- Update one target field in inline structure or sidecar metadata.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help recipes wrong-layer`

Sample:
- `ssd set meta:A1.confidence 0.91 --dry-run docs/examples/minimal.ssd`
